(1 + i)^{100}
(1+i)^2 = 2i
(1+i)^{100} = (2i)^{50} = 2^{50}\cdot (i)^{50} = -2^{50}
(1+i)^2=2i
(1+i)= \sqrt{2} \left(\dfrac1{\sqrt{2}} + i \dfrac1{\sqrt{2}} \right) = \sqrt{2} e^{i \pi/4}
(1+i)^{100} = 2^{50} e^{i \pi/4 \times 100} = 2^{50} e^{i25 \pi} = 2^{50} e^{i \pi} = - 2^{50}
